docs.abstract: Home innovations like smart microwaves and toilets could lock us into a digital caste system.
docs.snippet: Home innovations like smart microwaves and toilets could lock us into a digital caste system.
docs.lead_paragraph: A few months ago, Amazon invited reporters to its Spheres complex in downtown Seattle. It’s an enormous greenhouse doubling as a work space for employees: a climate-controlled, glass-enclosed, self-contained ecosystem made up of 40,000 species of plants from all over the world. Amazon executives opened the event with a statement worthy of their surroundings: The company had 70 products, services and tools to introduce. Seventy new products?  The journalists in the room responded with gasps and laughter.

headline.main: Are You an Amazon or an Apple Family?
headline.print_headline: Are You an Amazon or an Apple Family?

docs.abstract: The creators of a fairy-tale action film expand it into an eight-episode series by removing the fairy tale.
docs.snippet: The creators of a fairy-tale action film expand it into an eight-episode series by removing the fairy tale.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Hanna,” released in 2011, was not a film that called out for a remake or a sequel. It had a singular style, and a delicacy — despite its frequent beatdowns and gun battles — that would suffer from duplication. Bookended by parallel killings, it was a self-contained chronicle of an obsessive and successful quest for revenge that left no important questions unanswered.

headline.main: Review: Amazon’s ‘Hanna,’ Genetically Modified for Streaming Video
headline.print_headline: Take an Old Tale, Then Add Angst

docs.abstract: Amazon often plays politics with a distinctive message: Give us what we want, or we’ll leave and take our jobs elsewhere.
docs.snippet: Amazon often plays politics with a distinctive message: Give us what we want, or we’ll leave and take our jobs elsewhere.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — When Texas officials pushed Amazon to pay nearly $270 million in back sales taxes in 2010, Amazon responded by closing its only warehouse in the state and scrapping expansion plans there. Two years later, the officials agreed to waive the past taxes in exchange for Amazon opening new warehouses.

headline.main: Amazon’s Hard Bargain Extends Far Beyond New York
headline.print_headline: Amazon’s Offer To Cities: Take It Or We’ll Leave

docs.abstract: His tweets criticize Facebook and Google, but the Antitrust Division of the Justice Department is making life easier for potential monopolists in Silicon Valley.
docs.snippet: His tweets criticize Facebook and Google, but the Antitrust Division of the Justice Department is making life easier for potential monopolists in Silicon Valley.
docs.lead_paragraph: At his Senate confirmation hearing, Attorney General William Barr signaled an interest in confronting the power of big tech corporations like Facebook and Google. As Mr. Barr put it, a lot “of people wonder how such huge behemoths that now exist in Silicon Valley have taken shape under the nose of the antitrust enforcers.” And since taking office, President Trump has repeatedly attacked America’s biggest technology corporations, especially Amazon, Facebook and Google. Among other accusations, he has charged Amazon with ripping off the Post Office and Google with  censoring conservative users. He recently criticized Facebook, Google and Twitter for “ridiculous” bias in favor of Democrats. By most appearances, Mr. Trump is a foe of big tech.

byline.original: By Matthew Buck and Sandeep Vaheesan
